rComments: Dr. Shub was extremely helpful, not only for the courses that he teaches(which was linear algebra I for me) but would also help you on stuffs like advanced calculus. He was definately an awsome mathematician and a cool researcher back when he works for IBM!

Shub is atrocious. I think he would have failed the final, as whenever he did an example on the board, more often than not he ended up with the wrong answer due to an arithmetic error. He couldn't explain anything clearly, spoke quietly in a large room, and his handwriting was largely illegible. I hope for others' sakes he never teaches again!
Pretty sloppy lecturer, but helpful outside of class. Going to class is likely a waste of time provided that you have the textbook. A very average prof but definitely a mathematician.
Boring as hell, can't follow his lectures at all. No point of taking the course, might as well stay home and read the textbook.
A little too vague in lectures.  Always willing to help out students.  Overall a good prof.
